Re: Question...
by Feba » Sun 06.15.2008 12:45 am Mike Cash wrote:Horizontal right-to-left writing largely disappeared from common use many decades ago. The most common place you can see it still used is on the right side of trucks and other commercial vehicles....and not always then.Much in the way that military things with flag decorations tend to have it reversed on the right side?I have a question, though, are things written left to right published very often; and if they are, does the book have the binding on the left or right side?
Feba
