Re: Question...
by Hyperworm » Sun 06.15.2008 2:25 am To my knowledge, novels are almost always written vertically and bound on the right. If a book was written in the horizontal style, which would be common for books which necessarily must include a large amount of horizontal text (such as computer programming manuals), it would be bound on the left.
